# Website Rules (Next.js + Tailwind v4)

## Tailwind v4 Compatibility
- Use `@theme` in globals.css to register custom colors, NOT `:root` CSS variables for Tailwind classes
- Do NOT use `bg-clip-text` or `text-transparent` as Tailwind utilities — use the `.gradient-text` CSS class
- Do NOT use `text-[var(--name)]` or `bg-[var(--name)]/opacity` patterns — they break locally
- Use inline `style={{}}` for dynamic colors or CSS classes defined in globals.css
- Safe Tailwind classes: `text-white`, `text-white/80`, `bg-transparent`, standard colors

## Styling Approach
- CSS classes for reusable styles: `.card`, `.btn-primary`, `.btn-secondary`, `.badge-*`
- Inline `style={{}}` for one-off colors with rgba values
- Standard Tailwind for layout: flex, grid, spacing, border-radius, font-size

## Data Source Priority
1. Community database (Supabase RPCs) — always check first
2. iTunes Search API — fallback when DB has no match
3. YouTube oEmbed — for extracting video metadata from URLs

## Supabase Integration
- Use pre-configured client from `website/src/lib/supabase.ts`
- All DB access through RPCs: `find_mapping`, `find_mapping_by_apple_music`, `add_mapping`
- Auto-push matches from YouTube URL searches via `addMappingFromWebsite()` (fire-and-forget)
- Never block search results waiting for DB writes

## iTunes API
- Free, no API key needed, ~20 requests/minute soft limit
- Use `searchItunes()` for song search, `lookupByTrackId()` for metadata enrichment
- Always generate both web URL and `itmss://` native app URL

## Apple Music Links
- Web: `https://music.apple.com/us/song/{trackId}`
- Native app: `itmss://music.apple.com/us/song/{trackId}`
- Always provide both — native app for Mac/iOS users, web for others

## SEO
- Structured data (JSON-LD) for WebApplication and FAQPage in layout.tsx
- Meta tags, Open Graph, Twitter Cards all configured
- sitemap.ts and robots.ts for crawlers
- Landing page at `/youtube-to-apple-music` for targeted keywords
